snippet: Since bursting onto the scene as a precocious 10-year-old, Michelle Wie has won only two L.P.G.A. tournaments, but her play Friday put her one stroke behind the leader at the U.S. Women’s Open.
abstract: Michelle Wie has won only two LPGA tournaments since bursting on the scene in 2000, but her play at the United States Women's Open leaves her one stroke behind the second-round leader Suzann Pettersen.
lead_paragraph: Since bursting onto the scene as a precocious 10-year-old, Michelle Wie has won only two L.P.G.A. tournaments, but her play Friday put her one stroke behind the leader at the U.S. Women’s Open.

headline.seo: After Several Missed Cuts, Michelle Wie Is a Contender at the U.S. Open
headline.main: After 6 Missed Cuts This Season, Wie Is Again a Contender
headline.print_headline: After 6 Missed Cuts in 10 Events This Season, Wie Is Again a Contender
